From: Eliza Phase E <noreply@elizaos.dev>
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] omnivoice: share llama.cpp's backend pair (example)
Date: 2026-05-12

EXAMPLE PATCH — do not apply directly. Replaces omnivoice's
self-allocated `ggml_backend_t` pair with the shared backend owned by
the canonical llama.cpp build. This is the only invasive code change in
the merge — every other file is move-only.

Before:
  tools/omnivoice/src/backend.h calls ggml_backend_metal_init() /
  ggml_backend_cuda_init() / ggml_backend_vk_init() / ggml_backend_cpu_init()
  itself, depending on which CMake flags are set.

After:
  tools/omnivoice/src/backend.h takes a ggml_backend_t pair via a
  constructor parameter. ov_init() calls ggml_backend_load_all()
  (already present in llama.cpp) and picks the first GPU backend +
  the CPU fallback, the same way llama_context does internally.

This is what removes the duplicate GGML build: omnivoice no longer
needs its own ggml/ submodule, and the backend selection logic that
was scattered across omnivoice's buildcuda.sh / buildvulkan.sh /
buildmetal.sh becomes a single CMake-flag-driven path inherited from
llama.cpp.

---
 tools/omnivoice/src/backend.h      | 64 +++++++++++++-----------------
 tools/omnivoice/src/omnivoice.cpp  | 22 ++++++----
 2 files changed, 41 insertions(+), 45 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tools/omnivoice/src/backend.h b/tools/omnivoice/src/backend.h
--- a/tools/omnivoice/src/backend.h
+++ b/tools/omnivoice/src/backend.h
@@ -1,40 +1,30 @@
-// backend.h: omnivoice-private GGML backend selection.
-// Drops its own metal/cuda/vulkan/cpu init logic.
-// In the merged tree we receive the backend pair from llama.cpp.
+// backend.h: shared GGML backend pair from llama.cpp.
+// The merged build no longer owns its own backend init — it accepts
+// the pair the host llama_context already constructed and shares it
+// for the lifetime of the ov_context.
 #pragma once
 #include "ggml-backend.h"

 struct backend_pair {
-    ggml_backend_t gpu;  // metal / cuda / vulkan, or NULL
-    ggml_backend_t cpu;  // always present
+    ggml_backend_t gpu;  // borrowed, not owned
+    ggml_backend_t cpu;  // borrowed, not owned
 };

-backend_pair backend_init_auto(void);
-void         backend_free(backend_pair p);
+// Constructed from caller-provided handles; backend_pair_close is a no-op.
+inline backend_pair backend_from_borrowed(ggml_backend_t gpu, ggml_backend_t cpu) {
+    backend_pair p;
+    p.gpu = gpu;
+    p.cpu = cpu;
+    return p;
+}

